software: Admitted arsonist William Estel Benson sits in a police station after confessing to police that 24 years earlier he had sabotaged gas lines under a New London, Texas, school causing an explosion that killed 296 students and teachers on March 18, 1937. He said he wanted to "run up a gas bill," because he had been reprimanded for smoking. Oklahoma City, Oklahoma. July 18, 1961. Photo: Bettmann/Bettmann Archive
